  "chapter": {
    "number": 2,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Warning against Favoritism"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "My brothers, as you hold out your faith in our glorious Lord Jesus Christ, do not show favoritism."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "Suppose a man comes into your meeting",
          {
            "noteId": 2757
          },
          "wearing a gold ring and fine clothes, and a poor man in shabby clothes also comes in."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "If you lavish attention on the man in fine clothes and say, “Here is a seat of honor,” but say to the poor man, “You must stand” or “Sit at my feet,”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "have you not discriminated among yourselves and become judges with evil thoughts?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "Listen, my beloved brothers: Has not God chosen the poor of this world to be rich in faith and to inherit the kingdom He promised those who love Him?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "But you have dishonored the poor. Is it not the rich who oppress you and drag you into court?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "Are they not the ones who blaspheme the noble name by which you have been called?",
          {
            "noteId": 2758
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "If you really fulfill the royal law stated in Scripture, “Love your neighbor as yourself,”",
          {
            "noteId": 2759
          },
          "you are doing well."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "But if you show favoritism, you sin and are convicted by the law as transgressors."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "Whoever keeps the whole law but stumbles at just one point is guilty of breaking all of it."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "For He who said, “Do not commit adultery,”",
          {
            "noteId": 2760
          },
          "also said, “Do not murder.”",
          {
            "noteId": 2761
          },
          "If you do not commit adultery, but do commit murder, you have become a lawbreaker."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "Speak and act as those who are going to be judged by the law that gives freedom."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "For judgment without mercy will be shown to anyone who has not been merciful. Mercy triumphs over judgment."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Faith and Works"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "What good is it, my brothers, if someone claims to have faith, but has no deeds? Can such faith save him?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "Suppose a brother or sister is without clothes and daily food."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "If one of you tells him, “Go in peace; stay warm and well fed,” but does not provide for his physical needs, what good is that?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          "So too, faith by itself, if it does not result in action,",
          {
            "noteId": 2762
          },
          "is dead."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "But someone will say, “You have faith and I have deeds.” Show me your faith without deeds, and I will show you my faith by my deeds."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          "You believe that God is one.",
          {
            "noteId": 2763
          },
          "Good for you! Even the demons believe that—and shudder."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          "O foolish man, do you want evidence that faith without deeds is worthless?",
          {
            "noteId": 2764
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          "Was not our father Abraham justified by what he did when he offered his son Isaac on the altar?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          "You see that his faith was working with his actions, and his faith was perfected by what he did."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          "And the Scripture was fulfilled that says, “Abraham believed God, and it was credited to him as righteousness,”",
          {
            "noteId": 2765
          },
          "and he was called a friend of God.",
          {
            "noteId": 2766
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          "As you can see, a man is justified by his deeds and not by faith alone."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          "In the same way, was not even Rahab the prostitute justified by her actions when she welcomed the spies",
          {
            "noteId": 2767
          },
          "and sent them off on another route?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          "As the body without the spirit is dead, so faith without deeds is dead."
        ]
      }
    ],
